A full programme is attached.<br><br>The conference is free for academics and students (there is a small charge for practitioners), and all are welcome to attend. For catering purposes, please let Hannah Lynch &lt;hannah.lynch@ncl.ac.uk&gt; know if you intend to attend. Parking/Room Details. </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;12bf505.1412</link>   <description> Dear All,<br><br>Tomorrow the work in progress seminar will be held at York Law School in<br>LMB/145, starting at 12.00. This is on the first floor of the Law and<br>Management Building, and will be signposted from that floor.<br><br>Parking is available on the Heslington East car parks, however, it has been<br>impossible to get the barriers lifted. You will need to take a ticket from<br>the ticket machine to enter. You will need to pay to exit, however, the<br>Law School is happy to reimburse your parking costs. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-12-09T17:10:29+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Phillip Morgan</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;12bf505.1412</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;80d78451.1412">   <title>Programme for NEROG Work in Progress Seminar, York, 10th December </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;80d78451.1412</link>   <description> Dear All,<br><br>Please find enclosed below the programme for the NEROG Work in Progress<br>Seminar on 10th December at York Law School.<br><br>Programme:<br><br>12.00 \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd 12.40, David Pearce, (Leeds), \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd*OPO v MLA*: of wrong turns and<br>roads less travelled\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd.<br><br>(Lunch)<br><br>13.20 \ufffd\ufffd\ufffd 14.00, Phillip Morgan, (York), \ufffd\ufffd\ufffdJudgment Proofing of Non-Profits<br>and other Voluntary Sector Organisations from Liability in Tort\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-12-05T18:50:28+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Phillip Morgan</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;80d78451.1412</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;926ac93.1412">   <title>Re: NEROG Work in Progress Seminar </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;926ac93.1412</link>   <description> Dear All,<br><br>Thank you for responding on the Doodle Poll. To maximise the total numbers<br>present and also the number of presenters we are going for 10th December,<br>(the 18th is no longer available due to a newly added departmental<br>meeting). Details will follow soon as to programme and timings. If you<br>have indicated that you are willing to present at the session please would<br>you email me with the title of your paper by Friday. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-12-03T15:42:46+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Phillip Morgan</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;926ac93.1412</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;3a748f66.1411">   <title>NEROG Work in Progress Seminar </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;3a748f66.1411</link>   <description> Dear All,<br><br>I hope that all is well. We would like to host a NEROG work in progress<br>seminar/forum at York, ideally this December. This will be an informal<br>chance to give a paper, and to discuss obligations work in progress. To<br>try to find a date that as many people can make as possible I have created<br>a Doodle Poll with a range of options. If you would like to attend please<br>fill out all of the dates that you are able to make on the poll. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-11-30T14:13:33+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Phillip Morgan</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=NEROG;3a748f66.1411</dc:identifier> </item>   </rdf:RDF>
